>Jesse: AEINORR 4G OR +8 339
#note I have no idea if this was right. I played this because I saw only one E in the pool, and thought that it might be tough for Jakkrit to block column I (he'd have to be able to play his E at 3H). Perhaps I'll get to fish twice. On the flipside, NORIA at 3J turns over four tiles, maximizing my shot at the blank or Z if he missed them on his exchange (even drawing the H for 15A would be great). I have no idea how to quantify these two options - Quackle certainly doesn't. But what I will say from experience is that playing shorter and drawing out the game longer gives your opponent more time to make an error.
>Jakkrit: ?HIMNTZ 3F HM +21 361
#note he must block, and can't play HM at 15A. One suggestion was ZeNITH/HOY, which would've lost to ITERANCE!
>Jesse: AEEINRT 12J A... +5 344
#note whoof. None of my three RETINA bingos fits. ITERANCE does, but I actually didn't see it, and it's a losing play anyway unless the blank is in the bag (he gets devastating Z plays on row 1 if I play it). What I spotted at the time was that I had a sneaky draw for INERTIAE at 6H that I thought Jakkrit might miss under time pressure (he was down under a minute). I also saw that none of the RETINA bingos actually play on column I except for TANGIER and NATTIER, whereas EEINRT does hit column I with every letter except the Z. Against perfect play, I'm not sure that I can win unless I draw the blank.
>Jakkrit: ?GINNTZ 3I ZiNNI. +48 409
>Jesse: EEIINRT 6H INERTI.E +60 404
#note when the dust settled it looked like a tie, but it turned out that I had made three scoring errors: One in my favor, and the other two underscoring, and so this turned into a 1 point win. Wow!
